---
const experiences = [
  {
    role: 'Staff Software Engineer',
    promotedFrom: 'Senior Software Engineer',
    promotedDate: 'Oct 2025',
    company: 'Nium',
    period: 'Aug 2023 - Present',
    location: 'Hyderabad',
    highlights: [
      "The data team had no alerting - every pipeline failure landed as a Slack escalation at 2 AM. I built the entire observability stack from scratch: Datadog, Loki, PagerDuty, Grafana, Prometheus. 99.99% accuracy over 2.5 years. Escalations down 99%. The on-call now knows before anyone else does.",
      "Regulatory reporting was running on legacy Pentaho jobs nobody fully understood. I took ownership of the Safeguarding migration - read the legacy SQL line by line, pulled the right people into the room, and rebuilt it on Redshift. Compliance teams went from manual Excel checks to reliable dashboards. Any change now takes days, not sprints.",
      "Built a config-driven, multi-threaded S3-to-Redshift copy framework from scratch. No code change per new use case - just config. Handles millions of records, de-duplication, and parallel ingestion. It's now the backbone of core regulatory and analytical workloads. Presented it at TGIT - got personal appreciation from the Director.",
      "When an audit needed MasterCard transaction monitoring data backfilled from Jan 2024, the source team said 10 days. We delivered ~21M records in 2.5 hours. Zero exceptions. Audit closed successfully.",
      "Led the org-wide GenAI evaluation - compared Copilot, Cursor, and WinSurf on live engineering use cases from our own codebase. Engaged directly with CodeAnt's CEO. Recommended GitHub Copilot based on real evidence. Secured 50 licences for pilot rollout.",
    ],
    tags: ['Python', 'AWS', 'Redshift', 'Terraform', 'Datadog', 'PagerDuty', 'Loki', 'DMS', 'Glue', 'Lambda'],
    current: true,
  },
  {
    role: 'MTS-2',
    promotedFrom: 'MTS-1',
    promotedDate: null,
    company: 'Unravel Data',
    period: 'May 2021 - Aug 2023',
    location: 'Hyderabad',
    highlights: [
      `Took full ownership of the BigQuery pipeline - undocumented, single-threaded, built on fragile ObjectNode parsing that made testing nearly impossible. Refactored the entire codebase to type-safe POJOs, ported it into a dedicated Kafka worker with independent partitions, and scaled it to handle hundreds of concurrent GCP projects. Drove BigQuery from internal V1 to private preview across three major releases (4.7.3 to 4.7.5), trained the full cross-pillar team, and owned every architectural decision. Platform launch <a href="https://www.hpcwire.com/bigdatawire/this-just-in/unravel-data-launches-cloud-data-cost-observability-and-optimization-for-google-cloud-bigquery/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="highlight-link">covered by Datanami</a>. Won the Above and Beyond Award.`,
      "The night a major release shipped, a critical production issue hit. No handoff, no playbook. I debugged the failure, validated the fix across 10 customer clusters, and drove a clean build by morning.",
      "GCP project onboarding required 10 minutes of manual steps. I built a hackathon prototype that automated it end-to-end. It shipped as a core product feature in 4.7.5.0 - now the entry point for every new Unravel customer.",
      "Led the Snowflake pipeline from zero - requirements, data model, and initial delivery in 4.7.4.0. Defined from scratch how customer-environment metrics mapped to Unravel's schema.",
      "Was the sole Kafka SME. When production failures came in, I reproduced the exact customer environment locally and debugged at Java class level to trace the root cause - keeping enterprise pipelines stable without escalation.",
    ],
    tags: ['Java', 'Python', 'Kafka', 'BigQuery', 'Snowflake', 'Elasticsearch', 'OpenSearch', 'GCP', 'PostgreSQL'],
    current: false,
  },
  {
    role: 'Senior Product Developer',
    promotedFrom: 'Product Developer',
    promotedDate: null,
    company: 'Inncircles',
    period: 'June 2019 - April 2021',
    location: 'Hyderabad',
    highlights: [
      "Led the TechLearn edtech platform - an internal product for live online learning. Integrated the Zoom Web SDK end-to-end, letting users schedule, host, and join webinars without leaving the app.",
      "No security framework existed - access control was scattered across products. I designed and built the company-wide RBAC permissions framework from scratch. It became the single access control foundation across all products.",
      "Users in low-connectivity areas were getting logged out mid-session on a 6-hour token expiry. I built a refresh token framework supporting both web and mobile simultaneously, extending sessions to 30 days. Rolled out company-wide.",
      "API responses were inconsistent across services, causing constant frontend integration bugs. I designed and implemented a unified response and error-handling middleware - standardised all services, cut error rates by 40%.",
      "Led the in-house ticketing and support framework (similar to Jira) used by clients and internal teams. Mentored 3 engineers while delivering it end to end.",
    ],
    tags: ['MEAN Stack', 'Node.js', 'Angular', 'MongoDB', 'Express.js'],
    current: false,
  },
];
---

<section id="experience" class="exp-section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Experience</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Where I've<br /><span class="gradient-text">Worked</span></h2>
  </div>

  <div id="exp-scroll-wrapper" class="exp-scroll-wrapper">
    <div class="exp-sticky">
      <div class="container exp-inner">

        <nav class="exp-nav" aria-label="Experience navigation">
          <div class="progress-track" aria-hidden="true">
            <div id="exp-progress-fill" class="progress-fill"></div>
          </div>

          {experiences.map((exp, i) => (
            <button
              class={`exp-nav-item ${i === 0 ? 'active' : ''}`}
              data-index={i}
              aria-label={`View ${exp.role} at ${exp.company}`}
            >
              <span class="nav-index">0{i + 1}</span>
              <span class="nav-details">
                <span class="nav-role">{exp.role}</span>
                <span class="nav-company">{exp.company} · {exp.period}</span>
              </span>
            </button>
          ))}
        </nav>

        <div class="exp-panels">
          {experiences.map((exp, i) => (
            <div
              class={`exp-panel ${i === 0 ? 'active' : ''}`}
              data-panel={i}
              aria-hidden={i !== 0}
            >
              <div class="panel-eyebrow">
                <span class="panel-period">{exp.period}</span>
                <span class="panel-dot" aria-hidden="true" />
                <span class="panel-location">{exp.location}</span>
              </div>

              <h3 class="panel-role">{exp.role}</h3>

              {exp.promotedFrom && (
                <div class="promo-badge">
                  <span class="promo-from">{exp.promotedFrom}</span>
                  <span class="promo-arrow">→</span>
                  <span class="promo-to">{exp.role}</span>
                  {exp.promotedDate && <span class="promo-date">· {exp.promotedDate}</span>}
                </div>
              )}

              <p class="panel-company">{exp.company}</p>

              <ul class="panel-highlights">
                {exp.highlights.map(h => (
                  <li>
                    <span class="bullet" aria-hidden="true">▸</span>
                    <span set:html={h}></span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>

              <div class="panel-tags">
                {exp.tags.map((tag) => (
                  <span class="tag">{tag}</span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .exp-section { padding-bottom: 0; }

  .exp-scroll-wrapper {
    height: calc(3 * 100vh);
    position: relative;
  }

  .exp-sticky {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .exp-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
    width: 100%;
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  /* ── Left nav ── */
  .exp-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .progress-track {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 2px;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .progress-fill {
    width: 100%;
    height: 0%;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #06b6d4, #8b5cf6);
    border-radius: 2px;
    transition: height 0.08s linear;
  }

  .exp-nav-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    opacity: 0.3;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }

  .exp-nav-item.active { opacity: 1; }

  .nav-index {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-top: 3px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .nav-details {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .nav-role {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .nav-company {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  /* ── Right panels ── */
  .exp-panels {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 400px;
  }

  .exp-panel {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(20px);
    transition: opacity 0.4s ease, transform 0.4s ease;
    pointer-events: none;
    overflow-y: auto;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 14rem);
    padding-right: 1rem;
  }

  .exp-panel.active {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
    pointer-events: auto;
    position: relative;
  }

  .panel-eyebrow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .panel-period {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  .panel-dot {
    width: 4px;
    height: 4px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .panel-location {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .panel-role {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .promo-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-top: -0.25rem;
  }

  .promo-from {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .promo-arrow {
    color: var(--accent-2);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .promo-to {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #06b6d4, #8b5cf6);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .promo-date {
    color: var(--muted);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .panel-company {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .panel-highlights {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .panel-highlights li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .highlight-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .highlight-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .bullet {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }

  .panel-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .tag {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.07);
    border: 1px solid rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.18);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  /* ── Mobile fallback ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .exp-scroll-wrapper { height: auto; }
    .exp-sticky { position: relative; height: auto; padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
    .exp-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .exp-nav { display: none; }
    .exp-panels { min-height: unset; }
    .exp-panel {
      position: relative;
      opacity: 1;
      transform: none;
      pointer-events: auto;
      display: flex;
      max-height: none;
      padding-right: 0;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const wrapper = document.getElementById('exp-scroll-wrapper')!;
  const navItems = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.exp-nav-item');
  const panels = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.exp-panel');
  const progressFill = document.getElementById('exp-progress-fill')!;
  const count = panels.length;
  let currentIndex = 0;

  function setActive(index: number) {
    if (index === currentIndex) return;
    currentIndex = index;
    navItems.forEach((item, i) => item.classList.toggle('active', i === index));
    panels.forEach((panel, i) => {
      panel.classList.toggle('active', i === index);
      panel.setAttribute('aria-hidden', String(i !== index));
    });
  }

  function onScroll() {
    const rect = wrapper.getBoundingClientRect();
    const scrolled = -rect.top;
    const scrollable = rect.height - window.innerHeight;
    if (scrollable <= 0) return;

    const progress = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, scrolled / scrollable));
    progressFill.style.height = `${progress * 100}%`;

    const index = Math.min(count - 1, Math.floor(progress * count));
    setActive(index);
  }

  navItems.forEach((item) => {
    item.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const index = Number(item.dataset.index);
      const rect = wrapper.getBoundingClientRect();
      const scrollable = rect.height - window.innerHeight;
      const targetScroll = window.scrollY + rect.top + (index / count) * scrollable + 1;
      window.scrollTo({ top: targetScroll, behavior: 'smooth' });
    });
  });

  window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true });
  onScroll();
</script>
